#: prefs.js:899
msgid "Synced Lyrics"
msgstr "Paroles synchronisées"

#: prefs.js:901
msgid "Time-synced lyrics fetched from lrclib.net — free, no account needed"
msgstr "Paroles synchronisées récupérées de lrclib.net — gratuit, aucun compte requis"

#: prefs.js:907
msgid "Enable Synced Lyrics"
msgstr "Activer les paroles synchronisées"

#: prefs.js:909
msgid ""
"Fetch and display scrolling lyrics that follow the current playback position"
msgstr "Récupérer et afficher les paroles défilantes suivant la position de lecture"

#: prefs.js:926
msgid "How to Use Lyrics"
msgstr "Comment utiliser les paroles"

#: prefs.js:928
msgid ""
"Lyrics are tied to each player tab independently — Spotify and Firefox each "
"remember their own setting"
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:936
msgid "Start playing a song"
msgstr "Démarrer la lecture d'une chanson"

#: prefs.js:938
msgid ""
"Open any media player or browser tab (Spotify, YouTube Music, VLC, "
"Rhythmbox…) and play a track so it appears in the panel."
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:943
msgid "Open the popup player"
msgstr "Ouvrir le lecteur contextuel"

#: prefs.js:945
msgid ""
"Click the media controller icon in the top panel to open the popup. You’ll "
"see the album art, track title, and playback controls."
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:950
msgid "Triple-click the album art to show lyrics"
msgstr "Triple-cliquer sur la pochette pour afficher les paroles"

#: prefs.js:952
msgid ""
"Click the album art three times in quick succession. The cover image will be "
"replaced by the lyrics panel, which scrolls automatically in time with the "
"music."
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:957
msgid "Single-click the lyrics panel to go back"
msgstr "Cliquer une fois sur le panneau de paroles pour revenir"

#: prefs.js:959
msgid ""
"Tap anywhere on the lyrics panel once to dismiss it and return to the album "
"art — vinyl or normal cover, whichever that app uses."
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:964
msgid "Triple-click again to re-open"
msgstr "Triple-cliquer à nouveau pour rouvrir"

#: prefs.js:966
msgid ""
"You can toggle the lyrics panel as many times as you like. Each player tab "
"remembers independently whether lyrics are open."
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:986
msgid "Lyrics Behaviour"
msgstr "Comportement des paroles"

#: prefs.js:987
msgid "What happens behind the scenes"
msgstr "Ce qui se passe en arrière-plan"

#: prefs.js:992
msgid "Lyrics details & edge cases"
msgstr "Détails des paroles et cas limites"

#: prefs.js:993
msgid "What to expect when the lyrics panel is open"
msgstr "Ce à quoi s'attendre quand le panneau de paroles est ouvert"

#: prefs.js:999
msgid ""
"Source\n"
"  • Lyrics are fetched from lrclib.net — a free, open public database\n"
"  • No account or API key is required; the request is made silently in the "
"background\n"
"\n"
"Display\n"
"  • The active lyric line is shown larger and centred in the panel\n"
"  • The line above and below are shown at medium size; all others fade out\n"
"  • The panel scrolls smoothly so the active line is always in view\n"
"\n"
"Track changes\n"
"  • When a new song starts while the lyrics panel is open, the view clears\n"
"    and new lyrics are fetched automatically\n"
"  • If no lyrics are found, a “No lyrics found” message is shown\n"
"\n"
"Multiple players\n"
"  • Each player tab (Spotify, YouTube, VLC…) has its own independent\n"
"    lyrics toggle — opening lyrics for one player does not affect any other\n"
"  • Switching tabs restores the correct view (lyrics or album art) for\n"
"    the player you switch to\n"
"\n"
"Seeking\n"
"  • When you seek forward or backward, the highlighted line jumps\n"
"    instantly to the correct position"
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:1039
msgid "Album Art Click Actions"
msgstr "Actions de clic sur la pochette"

#: prefs.js:1041
msgid "Summary of what each click pattern does on the album art cover"
msgstr "Résumé des actions de chaque mode de clic sur la pochette"

#: prefs.js:1049
msgid "Single click"
msgstr "Clic simple"

#: prefs.js:1051
msgid ""
"When lyrics are showing: closes the lyrics panel and returns to the album art"
msgstr "Paroles affichées : ferme le panneau et revient à la pochette"

#: prefs.js:1056
msgid "Double click"
msgstr "Double clic"

#: prefs.js:1058
msgid ""
"Toggles the spinning vinyl record effect for that specific app (remembered "
"independently per app)"
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:1063
msgid "Triple click"
msgstr "Triple clic"

#: prefs.js:1065
msgid ""
"Toggles the synced lyrics panel for the current player tab (remembered "
"independently per player)"
msgstr ""

#: prefs.js:1084
msgid "Data Source"
msgstr "Source de données"

#: prefs.js:1085
msgid "Where lyrics come from"
msgstr "Origine des paroles"

#: prefs.js:1090
msgid "lrclib.net"
msgstr "lrclib.net"

#: prefs.js:1092
msgid ""
"Free, open-source time-synced lyrics database — no sign-up, no tracking, no "
"ads"
msgstr "Base de données de paroles synchronisées open source — sans inscription, sans suivi, sans publicité"

#: prefs.js:1120
msgid "Privacy note"
msgstr "Note de confidentialité"

#: prefs.js:1122
msgid ""
"A request containing the track title, artist, album and duration is sent to "
"lrclib.net when you open the lyrics panel. No personal data or user "
"identifiers are included."
msgstr ""

